The echo: false option disables the printing of code (only output is displayed). First I
need to install this package on my computer. To install any R package I use the function
install.packages()

#ggplot(cars)
Lets see how we can make this gure using ggplot
Before I can use any functions from add on packages I need to load the package from my
library() with the library(ggplot2) call.
library(ggplot2)
All ggplot gures have at least 3 things (called layers). These include
-data data (the input dataset I want to plot from) -aes (the aesthetic mapping of gthe data
to my plot) -geoms (the geom_point(), geom_line() etc. that I want to draw).
2
ggplot(cars) +
aes(x=speed, y=dist) +
geom_point() +
geom_smooth(method="lm") +
theme_bw()+
labs(title="My first GGPLOT")

n.tot <- nrow(genes)
vals <- table(genes$state)
vals.percent <- vals/n.tot * 100

A rst plot of this dataset
ggplot(genes) +
aes(x=Condition1, y=Condition2, col=State) +
geom_point() +
theme_bw() +
labs(title="Gene Expression changes upon drug treatment",
x="Control Expression",
y= "Drug Pressenence Expression") +
scale_color_manual( values=c("blue","gray","red") )
